                    Seeking friendly and outgoing Virtual Assistant experienced in U.S. residential real estate.

Want help growing business for this sole proprietor. Need part-time assistance in multiple areas of the business but primary focus is working existing leads. My focus is acquiring and reselling investment properties but I am also a licensed realtor who helps people buy and sell in retail market too. Assistance needed includes the following:

- Follow-up by text,
 and/or phone with leads to inquire about owner's desire to sell;

- Set appointments for me to meet with motivated sellers;

- Assistance with property research (looking up to see general information about the property, whether it is sold or available, and comparable prices)

- Track leads;

- Assist in uploading photographs, completing marketing packages, and documentation needed for selling properties; and,

- Potential assistance with my social media and other marketing initiatives...particularly getting Youtube channel started and video editing...but primary focus at the 
nt is lead gen follow-up;

- Assistance recruiting other real estate agents to join my team (using LinkedIn primarily for connecting with other agents across the US).



I am actively seeking to grow my team of licensed real estate agents in select markets. Need assistance contacting prospective agents via LinkedIn or other methods to establish relationships and set appointments for me to discuss opportunities with agency.



Initially, looking for part-time help of 10-20 hours per week...starting at 15 hours per week. Would like to pay a base hourly rate ($7) with a bonus structure for completed deals. Preference given to someone who has directly related experience in US residential real estate including phone sales. AND, previous experience with other real estate investors in the US is particularly helpful.



Specific skills needed include:

- Previous experience in residential real estate;

- Previous experience with phone sales including follow-up with contacts as well as cold calling leads;;

- Previous experience with appointment setting;

- Experience with Excel;

- Experience with agent recruiting (strongly preferred); and,

- Experience with social media marketing (preferred).



Attributes needed include:

- Pleasant, upbeat personality;

- Excellent relationship-building skills;

- Excellent phone skills including previous sales;

- Reliable;

- Hardworking;

- Empathy and understanding;

- Organized;

- Analytical including understanding of numbers;

- Able to work independently with minimal direction;

- Results oriented.



What you receive fro
 in return includes:

- Friendly and understanding colleague;

- Pleasant, enjoyable person to work with;

- Good teacher;

- Compensation structure that includes base hourly rate and potential bonus tied to properties we complete as a team.



Thanks for your considering. I look forward to hearing from you!
